column5: Who has Hydro ??  Just got a text message back from my Buddy who lives in Windermere, says he is still without power, I feel for him, he’s a stay at home day Dad, with a 1.5 year old on the loose.  And does some property maintenance for a few million dollar “cottages”.  I guess we lost power yesterday, only for 20 min.  How are you making out?  Entropy
out for 45 min. yesterday good today
Thank god I didnt lose power, I'd be pumping out my basement right about now!!
No problem here, never stopped for me.

All good here in Lindsay, a few short bumps yesterday but that was all. Sinker, if you are ever in a jam and need a generator let me know, I work for a rent all place so I can probably get my hands on a rental one for you on short notice and at whatever my boss would charge me for it. (probably free but if not, at a good discount).
Here's a link to the outage maps.  http://www.hydroonenetworks.com/en/about/o...s/south_map.asp  Entropy
All good here in Innisfil... didn't loose hydro at all...  thank god...
Just a tip, get a large boat bilge pump and a float switch, 12 volts and may save a flooded basement. You can always take a battery out of the boat or car to run it.
Out for about 5 hours yesterday..but good today!
That was alot of floods you guys had down there Shelly.

Cliff,  I will keep that in mind for sure!! TYVM for the offer!!    This I have for now.......two actually.....and a deep cycle battery for each one.......but if I'm not home when the water is flowing like it was yesterday......and the power goes out......I'm royally screwed!  Sinker
Power is good here. Lost power at work yesterday for about 45 mins. Last winter I lost power for over a day so I feel for those without. Hope all are back up soon.  Best Wishes: Rick
Came home early from Minnett area yesterday (power was out for a few hours and we decided to head back before dark) ... not sure if they have it back yet.
BC always has the best hydro
Haven't seen any interuption down here in the Niagara Peninsula at all.   Don
